EFS: (elastic file system)
=============================

- ebs/instance store will be stored in single server.
- efs is shared file system for ec2.
- storage capacity is elastic.
- supports NFS version 4.0 & 4.1 protocols when mounting.
- efs can be accessed by one or more ec2 instance at the same time.
- efs can be mounted on on-premises servers.
- can scale upto terabytes
- pay only for the amount of storage used.
- burst network performance upto 100MiB/s
- control file system access through POSIX permissions.
- vpc for network access control and IAM for API access control.
- encrypt data at rest using AWS KMS.
- use case : big data analytics, media processing workflows.
